##After the city was closed, I took the medical staff to and from work free of charge

Micro-signal Zairenjian11

Features, with a calm narrative against the cold | phoenix network produced in the human studio

1/7

If you don't do something for the city, in the end, maybe the city will die..

January 30,2020
@ Lei Feng Xiao Yang
COORDINATES: Wuhan

Please call me Lei Feng. I don't want to be remembered.

I'm from Wuhan. I work in hotel management. Our hotel is in the far city, and it's still open, so I use my spare time to shuttle the paramedics to and from work.

When I first heard the news about the closure of the city, I thought of the problem of medical staff and government employees going to work. On the morning of the 24th, I tweeted that doctors could be transported to and from work for free. Later, I found a group of volunteers, there are volunteers, there are also need to pick up the medical staff, people can communicate directly in the group, to inform the office hours and places and so on, so I am more involved in the volunteer transport.
We do not talk much in the car, usually just a simple talk or two, they are very tired at work, I am afraid to affect their rest.

But when I get to the station, I'll ask them for permission to take a picture together as a souvenir. Everyone I met was so keen that we left behind photos of ourselves together wearing masks.

I was particularly impressed by one of my fellow passengers, a young nurse, born in 1998 or 1999, who had volunteered for first line support at the Children's Hospital's rehabilitation unit. She had just applied that day and was probably on the front lines by now!

She said she had to walk an hour to and from work before I picked her up and dropped her off, which was hard for me to hear, driving and crying..
She even texted me the other day after we got off the bus, this really nice little nurse.

Because of the city closure, I have been staying at the hotel where I work and have not been able to go home to live with my parents. I told my family on the first day of volunteering to pick up and drop off medical staff that my parents were especially worried, so to speak, adamantly opposed. I didn't tell them for the next few days so they wouldn't worry. Even my colleagues don't know I'm doing this, and I worry about them, so I go around them.

Actually, I'm not too worried myself. I've been very protective of myself and others all the time. For example, when I drive, I roll down the window a little bit, not all the way in an enclosed space, and when people get out, I spray alcohol on the seats.

Now many hospitals also have shuttle buses, car demand than before, but I see a lot of doctors in the group still need to transport, so I will continue to do this thing when I have time.

Look at the masks I wear. Most of them are given to me by the paramedics I pick up and drop off.
So far, I've transported only a dozen paramedics. I read that there were about 5,000 volunteer car owners, and I thought I was 0.5 out of 5,000 because I picked up people who were closer to me. Some car owners in the group, see the need to help them will go to pick up, no matter the way is not on the way, no matter where, from them how far, go to pick up!

I was in the army, and now I've been gone for six or seven years, but I feel like I have a responsibility to do something, because it's one of the most rewarding things I've ever done.

Some things have to be done, do not do something for the city, in the end, the city may be finished..

People can't be together like they used to be, but at least they're together

This place is crazy
COORDINATES: Wuhan

January 26,2020
WECHAT received a call for help from a nurse in the Emergency Department of Hubei Provincial Hospital of Traditional Chinese medicine, Tanhualin Hospital, who lives alone in Pak Sha Chau, has no means of transportation, and now has no way to go to the hospital to work, asked the community and no taxi. I quickly sent a friend circle for help, what I did not expect is that the friend circle friends to help solve the problem very fast, more than a dozen people sent help information, the nurse's traffic problems were quickly solved. At that moment I feel small oneself can help, suddenly sense of responsibility, very happy. Today, motor vehicles are also banned in Wuhan City, I looked out the window, a quiet.

January 27,2020
Wake up in the morning, sleepy eyes, they hurried to see the latest news of the epidemic. On this day, in contrast to the outbreak, there was another piece of news that would make friends'circle of the frying pan: Bryant died in a plane crash. Oh, my God, 2020. What's going on.

Today is the 4th day after the city closed at home, my family did not go out for 3 days, feel almost suffocated, the family finally agreed to wear a mask, armed with running in the community. No one in the neighborhood goes downstairs, except for the cleaning crew. It's just us. The mothers strode forward, arm in arm. My wife and I cherish the time we can go downstairs, even three laps. After entering the house, the family hung their coats in the air, washed their hands and sprayed alcohol.

January 28,2020
This year's way of family New Year is video call, each family toast each other in the video new year, the mother smiled from ear to ear. Even though families can't be together like they used to be, at least they're together.

In the afternoon, we couldn't stay at home any longer, so we thought of Hoida near our home and met many stray children on the way. Some curl up outside the door, some snuggle together, some jump under the car as soon as they see someone coming. I suddenly realized that we were not the only ones alone in the city. There were thousands of them, and perhaps many more children who had been left behind by their owners and were being forced into "isolation" . On the way we met a kitten, actually followed us to walk 1 km... from the supermarket, I took just bought cat food and dog food, hope on the way home to do a small contribution.

The night is coming, expect to stray outside or be left at home by the master, no one loves the children can see the warm sun the next day.

3/7
For every normal person, taking care of yourself is doing the right thing

@ Freezing Point
COORDINATES: Wuhan
January 26,2020
Today is the fourth day of the siege. Except for my dad going to work on the night of New Year's Eve, none of us ever went out. From our home can see the third ring road in Wuhan, usually busy with traffic, but now only occasionally through the car, including ambulances. Community is no trace of people, in addition to the occasional occurrence of disinfection personnel, probably every family like us, like the small world in their own home.

In recent days, the friends circle is the lack of hospital supplies and private channels to raise the news. I see friends all over the world are concerned about Wuhan, the heart is a little touched. Many friends come to me every day and ask, how was your day? And every day I would reply to them: Today the situation is not good, but our family is normal. The outbreak is bad, but for everyone in the general population, to Take Care of ourselves is to do the right thing."In such a special moment, if we can not do the hero in the front line, to do the right thing properly, it is a kind of small greatness.

January 27,2020
On the third day of the Lunar New Year, Wuhan entered the Fifth Day of the blockade.

These days outside the window has been very gloomy, two days ago also under a light rain. The air conditioning was on, and my family spent the day on the Sofa. Mother said, This Day has let people not distinguish is the spring, Autumn or winter. Dad still cares about the potted daffodils, hope it can open a few more, bring some life to the home.

It seems that not only Wuhan, the whole country people in this Spring Festival are almost too busy to panic. I have friends in the group "Emoji War" , a friend to start a dialogue with Siri, and a friend said she "grew up in bed" , and play video games with her sister every day..

My parents didn't realize the severity of the outbreak until I got back, but they took it in stride after the lockdown. Our family is very quiet every day, as usual, the food is still enough to eat for a few days, we do not discuss the "closed city" when exactly will end. We just have to wait and see.

Thankfully, at this stage of the epidemic, I feel there is less talk of "conspiracy theories" and "second-guessing" , and more voice of reason to ask reasonable questions and discuss solutions. The group discussed more about what it would be like to go back north to Guangshen, and what to do after that.

January 28,2020
Wuhan entered the Sixth Day of the blockade. This morning, Wuhan finally had sunshine for a long time. The sunny days are always pleasant, but the outside world is as cold as ever.

Just last night, my family was watching TV when we heard a noise outside the window. I ran to the balcony, found that is the community in the shouting, men, women, adults, children are shouting "Wuhan Refueling" , but also mixed with some inaudible words. The last time I saw such a scene, it was before graduation when the various dormitories sang the Folk School Song.

In the afternoon, my parents still said, "the people of Wuhan Dare to let the premier shout slogans with them. ". Perhaps the prime minister's words "Go Wuhan" inspired everyone, at night, the students were locked in their homes for five days in Wuhan people finally could not help but vent a bit. But this venting behavior was quickly "expert advice" poured cold water, said that if upstairs and downstairs at the same time open the window, open mouth shouting songs, there is the risk of spreading droplets.
â–  outside, upstairs, it says, "Go Wuhan. ".

The good news came last night: I had a childhood friend in Xiangyang who had been frightened for days by a low fever. To avoid infecting her family, she moved into another house and ate alone on New Year's Eve. She got the results from the hospital yesterday and everything was fine! To her Get Well Soon!

January 29,2020
As usual, my family would sit on the SOFA together after dinner and do our own thing. "epidemic" will be a topic of discussion, but it will not be the only topic.

I often feel that in the unhappy days, it is more necessary to live happily. Don't deny yourself and others the right to be happy, and don't feel guilty that you're safe. Each of us calm is the first-line epidemic prevention staff the most solid backing, we more health and calm, the hospital will be less a hard work and chaos. Sometimes, the more chaotic the world is, the more power comes from an orderly routine.

If there is still room, everyone can do something for epidemic prevention. Even if it is to record a play and sing video at home to encourage more people, write a few diary articles to spread the Voice of the people of Wuhan, donate money or supplies to a trusted source, send greetings to the relatives and friends around... No matter how much impact these small actions can have, it can help you feel a little less powerless.

Last night, I listened to a song I loved for 15 years, from singer Jj Lin to medical workers on the front lines of the epidemic -- a Song I was deeply moved by. Sometimes the spirit is stronger than you think. In the face of COVID-19, we should neither fear it nor despise it. If every normal person can do it, maybe we'll be close to beating it.

Today is the fifth day of the Lunar New Year, the seventh day of the city closure in Wuhan. Today's Wuhan is also sunny, our whole family and healthy to spend a day together. Many years from now, when we look back on this year, and look back at the city's pain, we will remember that on that "special" Spring Festival, our city was not paralyzed, and we were not in a panic. We will remember, we will always believe in this city, we will always be with it.

5/7
I can't pay the rent. I'll give you more

January 27,2020
@ Zhang Heng
COORDINATES: Wuhan

Today saw the news that the bullet train back to Shanghai has stopped running, as scheduled back to Shanghai has no hope. Although I knew Wuhan had been sealed off, there was always a glimmer of luck, in case the epidemic suddenly improved. The News of the shutdown came as a full stop to my fantasy, telling me clearly that there was no going back.

I thought I could return to Shanghai as quickly as possible on the first day after the blockade was lifted. Opened 12306 ticket purchase software only to find that even if Wuhan can lift the blockade in mid-february, the entire February has no remaining tickets. Dad said, those who did not leave Wuhan as scheduled, will focus on the opening of a few days to leave Wuhan explosive. My mother comforted me and said, it doesn't matter, even if you can't buy a ticket, you can be the last one to go, or you can ask them to pay you less than a month's salary.

I picked up my mother's Fried Hongshan District sprouts and put them in my bowl. I bowed my head and ate without speaking. My mother suddenly said, "you will have no money to pay the rent, my mother will help you paste a bit. " I put the food into my mouth, looked up perfunctorily, "alas, we will talk about it then. " I thought to myself that my mother will always know what I was thinking.

6/7
This year's wish is simple: parents and loved ones are safe

January 29,2020
@ Ma Xiaoyu
Coordinates: Tianjin
Coordinates: Tianjin, home of three. I usually work outside, December twenty-six home, the epidemic has not been so serious. Seeing Wuhan's response "preventable and controllable, " I believed it. I didn't wear a mask on the bus ride home.

By December twenty-eight, the outbreak was so severe that the state media kept calling for a reduction in travel.

On the 12th month, twenty-nine, the city of Wuhan was closed.

This Day saw a lot of reports about the city closed, also believe a lot of rumors, the heart is very panic, in chat with friends I repeatedly said "PIA. ". As the online joke put it, "it's finally time to do nothing and contribute to our country. "

Near the New Year, there is a lot of stock, enough to eat about 20 days, so in addition to the daily garbage, my family and I are trying to avoid going out, so in the matter of wearing a mask, not too much conflict.

There is no seafood on the table at noon.

We gave up on crab and Stomatopoda when we learned of new cases of pneumonia in Tianjin, though seafood had nothing to do with COVID-19.

During the Spring Festival gala, give red envelopes to each other's parents. Unlike past blessings, this year's wish is simple: your parents and loved ones are safe.

New Year's Day at 3:00 pm, received a call from grandma, the village road closure, let us do not come over tomorrow. For the first time in my life, I didn't go back to my grandma's house.

Then has been "lying corpse" up to now, the daily activity track is basically: Bedroom, toilet, dining room, living room... circulation.

I want to say to all the medical staff who are struggling in the front line, "although we have never met, but you must be safe. ".

Mother said, This Day has let people not distinguish is the spring, Autumn or winter. Dad still cares about the potted daffodils, hope it can open a few more, bring some life to the home.

It seems that not only Wuhan, the whole country people in this Spring Festival are almost too busy to panic. I have friends in the group "Emoji War" , a friend to start a dialogue with Siri, and a friend said she "grew up in bed" , and play video games with her sister every day..

My parents didn't realize the severity of the outbreak until I got back, but they took it in stride after the lockdown. Our family is very quiet every day, as usual, the food is still enough to eat for a few days, we do not discuss the "closed city" when exactly will end. We just have to wait and see.

Thankfully, at this stage of the epidemic, I feel there is less talk of "conspiracy theories" and "second-guessing" , and more voice of reason to ask reasonable questions and discuss solutions. The group discussed more about what it would be like to go back north to Guangshen, and what to do after that.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wuhan entered the Sixth Day of the blockade. This morning, Wuhan finally had sunshine for a long time. The sunny days are always pleasant, but the outside world is as cold as ever.

Just last night, my family was watching TV when we heard a noise outside the window. I ran to the balcony, found that is the community in the shouting, men, women, adults, children are shouting "Wuhan Refueling" , but also mixed with some inaudible words. The last time I saw such a scene, it was before graduation when the various dormitories sang the Folk School Song.

In the afternoon, my parents still said, "the people of Wuhan Dare to let the premier shout slogans with them. ". Perhaps the prime minister's words "Go Wuhan" inspired everyone, at night, the students were locked in their homes for five days in Wuhan people finally could not help but vent a bit. But this venting behavior was quickly "expert advice" poured cold water, said that if upstairs and downstairs at the same time open the window, open mouth shouting songs, there is the risk of spreading droplets.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â–  outside, upstairs, it says, "Go Wuhan. ".

The good news came last night: I had a childhood friend in Xiangyang who had been frightened for days by a low fever. To avoid infecting her family, she moved into another house and ate alone on New Year's Eve. She got the results from the hospital yesterday and everything was fine! To her Get Well Soon!

January 29,2020
As usual, my family would sit on the SOFA together after dinner and do our own thing. "epidemic" will be a topic of discussion, but it will not be the only topic.

I often feel that in the unhappy days, it is more necessary to live happily. Don't deny yourself and others the right to be happy, and don't feel guilty that you're safe. Each of us calm is the first-line epidemic prevention staff the most solid backing, we more health and calm, the hospital will be less a hard work and chaos. Sometimes, the more chaotic the world is, the more power comes from an orderly routine.

If there is still room, everyone can do something for epidemic prevention. Even if it is to record a play and sing video at home to encourage more people, write a few diary articles to spread the Voice of the people of Wuhan, donate money or supplies to a trusted source, send greetings to the relatives and friends around... No matter how much impact these small actions can have, it can help you feel a little less powerless.

Last night, I listened to a song I loved for 15 years, from singer Jj Lin to medical workers on the front lines of the epidemic -- a Song I was deeply moved by. Sometimes the spirit is stronger than you think. In the face of COVID-19, we should neither fear it nor despise it. If every normal person can do it, maybe we'll be close to beating it.

Today is the fifth day of the Lunar New Year, the seventh day of the city closure in Wuhan. Today's Wuhan is also sunny, our whole family and healthy to spend a day together. Many years from now, when we look back on this year, and look back at the city's pain, we will remember that on that "special" Spring Festival, our city was not paralyzed, and we were not in a panic. We will remember, we will always believe in this city, we will always be with it.

5/7
I can't pay the rent. I'll give you more

January 27,2020
@ Zhang Heng
COORDINATES: Wuhan

Today saw the news that the bullet train back to Shanghai has stopped running, as scheduled back to Shanghai has no hope. Although I knew Wuhan had been sealed off, there was always a glimmer of luck, in case the epidemic suddenly improved. The News of the shutdown came as a full stop to my fantasy, telling me clearly that there was no going back.

I thought I could return to Shanghai as quickly as possible on the first day after the blockade was lifted. Opened 12306 ticket purchase software only to find that even if Wuhan can lift the blockade in mid-february, the entire February has no remaining tickets. Dad said, those who did not leave Wuhan as scheduled, will focus on the opening of a few days to leave Wuhan explosive. My mother comforted me and said, it doesn't matter, even if you can't buy a ticket, you can be the last one to go, or you can ask them to pay you less than a month's salary.

I picked up my mother's Fried Hongshan District sprouts and put them in my bowl. I bowed my head and ate without speaking. My mother suddenly said, "you will have no money to pay the rent, my mother will help you paste a bit. " I put the food into my mouth, looked up perfunctorily, "alas, we will talk about it then. " I thought to myself that my mother will always know what I was thinking.

This year's wish is simple: parents and loved ones are safe

@ Ma Xiaoyu

Coordinates: Tianjin

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Coordinates: Tianjin, home of three. I usually work outside, December twenty-six home, the epidemic has not been so serious. Seeing Wuhan's response "preventable and controllable, " I believed it. I didn't wear a mask on the bus ride home.

By December twenty-eight, the outbreak was so severe that the state media kept calling for a reduction in travel.

On the 12th month, twenty-nine, the city of Wuhan was closed.

This Day saw a lot of reports about the city closed, also believe a lot of rumors, the heart is very panic, in chat with friends I repeatedly said "PIA. ". As the online joke put it, "it's finally time to do nothing and contribute to our country. "

Near the New Year, there is a lot of stock, enough to eat about 20 days, so in addition to the daily garbage, my family and I are trying to avoid going out, so in the matter of wearing a mask, not too much conflict.

There is no seafood on the table at noon.

We gave up on crab and Stomatopoda when we learned of new cases of pneumonia in Tianjin, though seafood had nothing to do with COVID-19.

During the Spring Festival gala, give red envelopes to each other's parents. Unlike past blessings, this year's wish is simple: your parents and loved ones are safe.

New Year's Day at 3:00 pm, received a call from grandma, the village road closure, let us do not come over tomorrow. For the first time in my life, I didn't go back to my grandma's house.

Then has been "lying corpse" up to now, the daily activity track is basically: Bedroom, toilet, dining room, living room... circulation.

I want to say to all the medical staff who are struggling in the front line, "although we have never met, but you must be safe. ".

7/7
As long as you have a bite to eat, don't go out. Remember! Remember!

January 29,2020
@ 11 pairs of friends
COORDINATES: Wuhan

A hospital doctor warned: "The next two days is an outbreak, a large number of incubation period will show up, nearly a week everyone do not go out, as long as there is a bite to eat, we must not go out. Remember! Remember! "

One day at home is fine. Two days is fine. Three days, four days? After a while, it's like going to jail. The outbreak has not only prompted some officials to reflect, and perhaps even punish, but has also left ordinary people to ponder: what is most important when one is alive?
